        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 2:16PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waldron, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stonehouse Recreation Area...     Union Hill...
Mount Magazine...                 Wing...
Cardiff...                        Waveland...
Olio...                           Cedar Creek...
Waltreak...                       Waldron...
Bluffton...                       Nola...
Blue Mountain...                  Needmore...
Harvey...                         Sugar Grove...
Gravelly...                       Parks...
Briggsville...                    Fourche Valley...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for western and
central Arkansas.</instruction>
